        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 10:49AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 1048 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Horatio, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eagletown, Lockesburg, Cerrogordo, De Queen, Oak Grove, Geneva,
Central, Foreman, Goodwater, Shinewell, Arkinda, Wallace, Horatio,
West Line, Winthrop, Bellview, West Otis, and Ben Lomond.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 PM CDT for
southwestern Arkansas...and southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
